
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dpkg-deb` baraye dorost kardan, baz kardan va modiriyat kardan file-haye `.deb` (Debian package) estefade mishavad. File-haye `.deb` baraye nasb kardan narmafzar dar system-haye Debian va Ubuntu be kar miravand. In dastoor bishtar baraye sakhtan ya baz kardan package-ha be soorate manual estefade mishavad.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `dpkg-deb -b <directory> <file.deb>`  --> 📦 Sakhtan yek file `.deb` az yek directory.
    🔹 `dpkg-deb -x <file.deb> <directory>`  --> 📂 Baz kardan file `.deb` va extract kardane an be yek directory.
    🔹 `dpkg-deb -I <file.deb>`  --> ℹ️ Namayesh etela'at darbareye package (mesle name, version, dependencies).
    🔹 `dpkg-deb --contents <file.deb>` --> 📃 List kardane file-haye dakhele package.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dpkg-deb -b mypackage mypackage.deb

    🔹 Sakhtan yek package `.deb` az directory "mypackage" va save kardane an be name "mypackage.deb".

    $ dpkg-deb -x mypackage.deb extracted_package

    🔹 Baz kardan file "mypackage.deb" va extract kardane hameye file-ha dar directory "extracted_package".

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ dpkg-deb -I mypackage.deb

    🔹 Namayesh etela'ati mesle name package, version va etela'ate digar darbareye package "mypackage.deb".

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dpkg-deb` command is used to create, unpack, and manage `.deb` (Debian package) files. `.deb` files are used for installing software on Debian and Ubuntu-based systems. This command is primarily used for manually building or inspecting packages.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `dpkg-deb -b <directory> <file.deb>`  --> 📦 Build a `.deb` file from a directory.
    🔹 `dpkg-deb -x <file.deb> <directory>`  --> 📂 Extract a `.deb` file and unpack it into a directory.
    🔹 `dpkg-deb -I <file.deb>`  --> ℹ️ Show information about the package (e.g., name, version, dependencies).
    🔹 `dpkg-deb --contents <file.deb>` --> 📃 List the files contained within the package.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dpkg-deb -b mypackage mypackage.deb

    🔹 Creates a `.deb` package from the "mypackage" directory and saves it as "mypackage.deb".

    $ dpkg-deb -x mypackage.deb extracted_package

    🔹 Extracts the contents of the "mypackage.deb" file into the "extracted_package" directory.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ dpkg-deb -I mypackage.deb

    🔹 Displays information such as the package name, version, and other details about the "mypackage.deb" package.
